GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 476
Short Title: Allow Widow/Widower To Hyphenate Name. (Public)
Sponsors: Senator Murdock (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
March 25, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO ALLOW A WIDOW OR WIDOWER TO HYPHENATE PRE-MARRIAGE AND
3 MARRIED SURNAMES.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. G.S. 101-8 reads as rewritten:
6 "§ 101-8. Resumption of name by widow or widower.
7 A person at any time after the person is widowed may, upon application to the clerk of court
8 of the county in which the person resides setting forth the person's intention to do so, resume the
9 use of her maiden name or the name of a prior deceased husband or of a previously divorced
10 husband in the case of a widow, or his premarriage surname in the case of a widower. change the
11 person's name to his or her (i) pre-marriage surname, (ii) pre-marriage surname joined by a
12 hyphen to the surname of the last spouse of the person, or (iii) the surname of a previously
13 deceased or divorced spouse. The application shall set forth the full name of the last spouse of
14 the applicant, shall include a copy of the spouse's death certificate, and shall be signed by the
15 applicant in the applicant's full name. If the applicant seeks a name change to the surname of a
16 previously divorced spouse who is still living, the applicant shall include an affidavit signed by
17 the previously divorced spouse consenting to the applicant's name change. The clerks of court of
18 the several counties of this State shall record and index such applications in the manner required
19 by the Administrative Office of the Courts."
20 SECTION 2. This act is effective when it becomes law.
*S476-v-1*

